{"author":{"id":"2d08e4816aca0a07db9878f126b0e7f6d6f1362eb9bc4804be6b33ff8d0a19ec"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1715743877,"nonce":"pB8Xw4YA/kLn2vNiZOpTYcgbPWs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOJl1IZM6I5jWa","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/226","origin":"github"},"title":"Add a possibility to \"await\" the moment when new window opens","message":"## Problem\n\nSuppose the user wants to open a new window and move to the particular workspace. \n\nThe naive solution won't work because `open` finishes faster than the window appears:\n```\nopen -n /Applications/kitty.app \u0026\u0026 aerospace move-node-to-workspace kitty\n```\n\n## Proposed solutions\n\n**Solution 1.** \"callback\" style command to run next commands once focus changes\n```\nopen -n /Applications/kitty.app \u0026\u0026 aerospace run-when-focus-changes move-node-to-workspace kitty\n```\n\n**Solution 2.** \"suspend\" style command to await until the next window appears. (Harder to implement but prettier)\n```\nopen -n /Applications/kitty.app \u0026\u0026 aerospace await-focus-changed \u0026\u0026 aerospace move-node-to-workspace kitty\n```","files":null}]}